<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1438,152,758]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,330,654,680]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Discussion</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName box="[367,646,655,680]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hezhouense">
<emphasis box="[367,646,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Elatostema hezhouense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Schroeter (1939)" authorityName="Schroeter" authorityYear="1939" box="[881,1367,654,680]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ichangense">
<emphasis box="[881,1156,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Elatostema ichangense</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schroeter, H." box="[1167,1367,654,680]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="220 - 221" refId="ref10490" refString="Schroeter, H. (1939) Nonnullae descriptiones specium novarum generis Elatostema subgen Eulatostema. Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 47: 220 - 221." type="journal article" year="1939">Schroeter (1939)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from which it can be distinguished based on leaf base and pistillate inflorescence morphology and the distribution of pistillate and staminate inflorescences as summarised in the table below:
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<table box="[165,1418,835,1113]" gridcols="3" gridrows="6" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<tr box="[165,1418,835,859]" gridrow="0" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rowspan-0="1">
<td box="[706,1054,835,859]" gridcol="1" gridrow="0" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName box="[706,964,835,859]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hezhouense">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[706,964,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Elatostema hezhouense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</td>
<td box="[1088,1418,835,859]" gridcol="2" gridrow="0" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schroeter" authorityYear="1939" box="[1088,1341,835,859]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ichangense">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1088,1341,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Elatostema ichangense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[165,1418,865,888]" gridrow="1" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<td box="[165,672,865,888]" gridcol="0" gridrow="1" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Tertiary and quarternary veins of upper surface</td>
<td box="[706,1054,865,888]" gridcol="1" gridrow="1" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">raised and prominent</td>
<td box="[1088,1418,865,888]" gridcol="2" gridrow="1" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">neither raised nor prominent</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[165,1418,912,935]" gridrow="2" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<td box="[165,672,912,935]" gridcol="0" gridrow="2" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Leaf base</td>
<td box="[706,1054,912,935]" gridcol="1" gridrow="2" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">broader side distinctly auriculate</td>
<td box="[1088,1418,912,935]" gridcol="2" gridrow="2" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">broader side obtuse or rounded</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[165,1418,960,983]" gridrow="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<td box="[165,672,960,983]" gridcol="0" gridrow="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Pistillate peduncle</td>
<td box="[706,1054,960,983]" gridcol="1" gridrow="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">0.7–2.0 mm</td>
<td box="[1088,1418,960,983]" gridcol="2" gridrow="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">6–10 mm</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[165,1418,1007,1030]" gridrow="4" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<td box="[165,672,1007,1030]" gridcol="0" gridrow="4" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Pistillate receptacle diameter</td>
<td box="[706,1054,1007,1030]" gridcol="1" gridrow="4" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">2.0–3.5 mm</td>
<td box="[1088,1418,1007,1030]" gridcol="2" gridrow="4" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">3–8 mm</td>
